claim.OtherNoPaymentReason, claim.LossNoticeNumber, claim.RowId ,
claimPolicyInfo.policynumber,
case when length(claimPolicyInfo.policyversion)='1' then concat('00',claimPolicyInfo.policyversion)
when length(claimPolicyInfo.policyversion)='2' then concat('0',claimPolicyInfo.policyversion)
else claimPolicyInfo.policyversion end as policyversion, case when claim.typecd='Claim' then PolicyRisk.RiskIdRef else null end as PolicyRiskIdref, UnderlyingPersonalLiability FROM
 claim left join (Select PolicyNumber,PolicyVersion, SystemId, UnderlyingPersonalLiability from claimPolicyInfo where  ClaimPolicyinfo.cmmcontainer='Claim') ClaimPolicyInfo on 
Claim.Systemid=ClaimPolicyinfo.Systemid 
Left join (select systemid,id, riskidref from PolicyRisk) PolicyRisk on claim.riskidref = PolicyRisk.id 
where 
claim.cmmcontainer='Claim' and claim.systemid in (select systemid from advrxxchangedbeans where concat(adddt,addtm)>='$$m_strtdt' and 
concat(adddt,addtm) <='$$m_Enddt' and
 cmmcontainer='Claim')

transformations.description: This reusable expression will properly check and format up to 5 dates that may be in the 'YY-MM-DD' format. It assumes that any years before '50 are in the current century, and any years after '50 are in the previous century.
transformations.name: Exp_format_date3

fields.name: v_Date1
fields.expression: TO_CHAR(in_Date1, 'YYYY-MM-DD')

fields.name: out_Date1
fields.expression:
IIF(ISNULL(in_Date1), NULL,
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 0, 2) = '00', 
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3, 2) <= '50', TO_DATE(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YY-MM-DD'), TO_DATE('19' || SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YYYY-MM-DD')),
IIF(IS_DATE(v_Date1, 'YYYY-MM-DD') and DATE_COMPARE(in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD')) > 0 , in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD'))))
